# NEVER commit the raw genealogy data — it contains unredacted details for people
# who are still living. Only dist/ (the redacted public build) is published.
src/*.ged
src/*.gedcom
data/gedcom.json
data/problems.txt
data/places-unresolved.json

# The ROOT familydata.js is the FULL build — living people are NOT redacted (it is
# what preview.html uses locally, and what gets pushed to the private claude.ai
# design project). Only docs/familydata.js, the redacted build, may be committed.
#
# The leading slash ANCHORS this to the repo root. Without it the pattern matches
# at every level and silently swallows docs/familydata.js too — which published a
# site with no data in it.
/familydata.js

# local-only full-data preview (living people NOT redacted)
preview.html
_probe.html
_v_*.html
_diag.html
_cdn.html

*.bak
dist/

# Working copies of the record scans and photographs. These are GENERATED from
# Roots/Thompson Family Tree_media by Match-Media.ps1 / Match-Records.ps1, and
# Build-Site copies them into docs/. Committing both would put ~90 MB in the repo
# twice over. Only the published copy (docs/img/) is tracked.
img/media/
img/records/
img/people/

# the RootsMagic database — an input to the build, like the GEDCOM. Never publish:
# it holds living people's details.
*.rmtree
